Third-party components

The source in this repository is MIT-licensed. The prebuilt binary
(ffmpeg.node) statically links third-party libraries under their own licenses:

  - FFmpeg (libavformat/libavcodec/libavutil/libswscale/libswresample),
    built WITHOUT --enable-gpl, under the LGPL-2.1-or-later.
  - OpenH264 (https://github.com/cisco/openh264), under the BSD-2-Clause.

The complete corresponding source and the scripts used to build these
libraries are published with this package (see scripts/), satisfying the
LGPL's relinking requirements. Note that H.264 is patent-encumbered; OpenH264's
royalty-free terms apply to Cisco's distributed binary module, not to binaries
you compile yourself — review your own H.264 patent obligations if relevant.
